not listening to me

79
00:05:05,929 --> 00:05:07,363
and doing what he was told.

80
00:05:07,396 --> 00:05:10,363
KURODO: [chuckles] You're
OK, right, Yumichika?

81
00:05:10,396 --> 00:05:11,429
NOBA: Of course, he is.

82
00:05:11,463 --> 00:05:12,563
-Don't worry.

83
00:05:12,596 --> 00:05:14,129
Once he comes to, I'm
sure he'll forgive us.

84
00:05:14,163 --> 00:05:16,529
-Urrh, rrahh!

85
00:05:16,563 --> 00:05:18,496
[shrieks]

86
00:05:18,529 --> 00:05:19,496
RIRIN: Run for it!

87
00:05:19,529 --> 00:05:20,496
KURODO: We're sorry!

88
00:05:20,529 --> 00:05:21,629
Just doing--

89
00:05:21,663 --> 00:05:23,496
NOBA: Does this mean
you're not forgiving us?

90
00:05:23,529 --> 00:05:25,929
-If I catch you, I'm going
to turn you inside out.

91
00:05:25,963 --> 00:05:27,296
By the time I'm
through with you,

92
00:05:27,329 --> 00:05:29,296
there won't be enough
piece of what to identify.

93
00:05:29,329 --> 00:05:32,696
Come back here and
face me, you maggots!

94
00:05:32,729 --> 00:05:34,463
-That was predictable.

95
00:05:34,496 --> 00:05:38,263
They always get so
manic wherever they go.

96
00:05:38,296 --> 00:05:40,596
[whooshing wind]

97
00:05:42,996 --> 00:05:44,463
TOSHIRO (VOICEOVER):
I wonder what's

98
00:05:44,496 --> 00:05:46,796
going on up there
with Kisuke Urahara.

99
00:05:46,829 --> 00:05:49,829
He's been very quiet
since the fight ended.

100
00:05:49,863 --> 00:05:51,229
He's such a mystery.

101
00:05:51,263 --> 00:05:53,196
I know he's had
something on his mind

102
00:05:53,229 --> 00:05:56,329
since the Arrancars retreated.

103
00:05:56,363 --> 00:05:58,096
Maybe he's planning
our next offensive.

104
00:05:58,129 --> 00:06:00,029
I know one thing, though.

105
00:06:00,063 --> 00:06:02,763
For having fought so
many of the Espada,

106
00:06:02,796 --> 00:06:06,429
we're lucky that this is
all the damage we suffered.

107
00:06:06,463 --> 00:06:09,229
We were careless, and
we underestimated them.

108
00:06:09,263 --> 00:06:10,596
They had prepared
for the battle.

109
00:06:10,629 --> 00:06:12,263
And we hadn't.

110
00:06:12,296 --> 00:06:13,696
We're going to
have to work harder

111
00:06:13,729 --> 00:06:15,863
to be ready for the
next encounter, whenever

112
00:06:15,896 --> 00:06:17,629
that may be.

113
00:06:17,663 --> 00:06:19,963
I just wonder if we'll have
time to do what's necessary

114
00:06:19,996 --> 00:06:21,963
before they come at us again.

115
00:06:21,996 --> 00:06:26,596
How long will it take before
we can get up the strength?

116
00:06:26,629 --> 00:06:27,196
-Rangiku.

117
00:06:27,229 --> 00:06:28,396
-[gasps]

118
00:06:28,429 --> 00:06:29,663
Yes?

119
00:06:29,696 --> 00:06:32,363
-Have you been able to
contact the Soul Society yet?

120
00:06:32,396 --> 00:06:33,629
-No, I'm not having any luck.

121
00:06:33,663 --> 00:06:35,096
[beeps]

122
00:06:35,129 --> 00:06:38,529
[static noise]

123
00:06:44,429 --> 00:06:44,896
-Hm.

124
00:06:48,363 --> 00:06:49,796
[gasps]

125
00:06:49,829 --> 00:06:51,763
Uh, I'm so sorry.

126
00:06:51,796 --> 00:06:53,229
-Huh?

127
00:06:53,263 --> 00:06:53,963
-Hey, what's up?

128
00:06:53,996 --> 00:06:54,996
What are you looking at?

129
00:06:55,029 --> 00:06:56,963
-It felt like I
bumped into something,

130
00:06:56,996 --> 00:06:58,529
but I can't see what it was.

131
00:06:58,563 --> 00:06:59,763
-What are you talking about?

132
00:06:59,796 --> 00:07:00,829
There's nothing near you.

133
00:07:00,863 --> 00:07:02,063
Are you going nuts on me?

134
00:07:02,096 --> 00:07:02,663
-I don't know.

135
00:07:02,696 --> 00:07:03,729
Maybe.

136
00:07:03,763 --> 00:07:05,029
I thought I hit something.

137
00:07:05,063 --> 00:07:06,829
It was a weird feeling,
that's for sure.

138
00:07:06,863 --> 00:07:09,029
It felt kind of
soft and squishy.

139
00:07:22,863 --> 00:07:23,796
[gasps]

140
00:07:23,829 --> 00:07:24,963
ULQUIORRA (VOICEOVER):
You will be

141
00:07:24,996 --> 00:07:27,029
invisible to the outside world.

142
00:07:27,063 --> 00:07:31,896
Only we, Arrancars, will
be aware of your presence.

143
00:07:31,929 --> 00:07:34,763
You'll find you have
one more ability.

144
00:07:34,796 --> 00:07:36,896
While you have it on,
you'll be able to pass

145
00:07:36,929 --> 00:07:39,829
through any physical object
that exists in your world.

146
00:08:03,896 --> 00:08:04,329
-Hm.

147
00:08:08,863 --> 00:08:11,896
BOY 1: [singing] I'm sure
I left it in my desk.

148
00:08:11,929 --> 00:08:13,596
BOY 2: Good thing your
head's screwed on,

149
00:08:13,629 --> 00:08:14,863
or you can misplace that, too.

150
00:08:14,896 --> 00:08:16,096
BOY 1: [singing] I forgot it.

151
00:08:16,129 --> 00:08:17,529
I forgot it!

152
00:08:17,563 --> 00:08:19,929
BOY 2: Would you
please not sing that.

153
00:08:19,963 --> 00:08:21,829
It's irritating.

154
00:08:21,863 --> 00:08:22,329
-Uhh.

155
00:08:25,229 --> 00:08:26,829
--[singing] He, he
forgot something.

156
00:08:26,863 --> 00:08:28,996
He, he forgot something!

157
00:08:29,029 --> 00:08:32,096
-Mr. Asano, will
you stop singing?

158
00:08:32,129 --> 00:08:33,963
ORIHIME (VOICEOVER):
Uh, why am I hiding?

159
00:08:33,996 --> 00:08:35,363
They can't see me.

160
00:08:35,396 --> 00:08:36,763
-I thought I told you.

161
00:08:36,796 --> 00:08:39,596
Stop being so formal,
calling me by my last name.

162
00:08:39,629 --> 00:08:41,529
I mean, we're
friends, aren't we?

163
00:08:41,563 --> 00:08:42,363
-Of course, we are.

164
00:08:42,396 --> 00:08:44,063
You certainly are touchy today.

165
00:08:44,096 --> 00:08:46,696
-You don't know the
pressure I'm under.

166
00:08:46,729 --> 00:08:47,196
-Huh?

167
00:08:47,229 --> 00:08:49,329
-What is it?

168
00:08:49,363 --> 00:08:50,429
-That's weird.

169
00:08:50,463 --> 00:08:52,896
I wonder why Ichigo's
chair fell over.

170
00:08:52,929 --> 00:08:54,529
You think he came
to school today?

171
00:08:54,563 --> 00:08:56,029
-No way.

172
00:08:56,063 --> 00:08:58,796
Someone must have just
bumped into it or something.

173
00:08:58,829 --> 00:08:59,496
-Hm.

174
00:08:59,529 --> 00:09:00,829
I guess.

175
00:09:00,863 --> 00:09:04,629
But don't you think it's
strange that he, Chad, Orihime,

176
00:09:04,663 --> 00:09:08,529
Rukia, and Uryu were all absent
from school on the same day?

177
00:09:08,563 --> 00:09:09,096
-Hrrh!

178
00:09:09,129 --> 00:09:10,329
Wait, that's it!

179
00:09:10,363 --> 00:09:13,263
They're all doing something
fun together. [bawls]

180
00:09:13,296 --> 00:09:14,696
And we've been left out.

181
00:09:14,729 --> 00:09:16,596
The cool kids are
deliberately snubbing us.

182
00:09:16,629 --> 00:09:18,496
-Don't put me in the
same group as you.

183
00:09:18,529 --> 00:09:21,029
-What's that?

184
00:09:21,063 --> 00:09:22,396
MIZUIRO: And besides--

185
00:09:22,429 --> 00:09:24,596
-Huh?

186
00:09:24,629 --> 00:09:27,029
-If you take a minute
to think about it,

187
00:09:27,063 --> 00:09:29,529
we're not the only ones
who have been left out.

188
00:09:29,563 --> 00:09:30,463
-Oh, really?

189
00:09:30,496 --> 00:09:31,896
-Well, what do you mean?

190
00:09:31,929 --> 00:09:33,429
Like who?

191
00:09:33,463 --> 00:09:36,963
-Off the top of my head, the
first one who comes to mind

192
00:09:36,996 --> 00:09:38,463
is Tatsuki.

193
00:09:38,496 --> 00:09:38,963
-Uh.

194
00:09:52,729 --> 00:09:55,563
MIZUIRO (VOICEOVER): If you
take a minute to think about it,

195
00:09:55,596 --> 00:10:00,263
we're not the only ones
who have been left out.

196
00:10:00,296 --> 00:10:03,596
Off the top of my head, the
first one who comes to mind

197
00:10:03,629 --> 00:10:04,596
is Tatsuki.

198
00:10:11,563 --> 00:10:14,029
-[panting]

199
00:10:19,496 --> 00:10:20,463
-Keep up your pace.

200
00:10:20,496 --> 00:10:21,929
Don't slack off now.

201
00:10:21,963 --> 00:10:22,929
GROUP: Yes, sir!

202
00:10:26,929 --> 00:10:27,396
-Uh.

203
00:10:34,396 --> 00:10:36,363
Tatsuki.

204
00:10:36,396 --> 00:10:37,363
[gasps]

205
00:10:40,863 --> 00:10:41,296
Uh.

206
00:10:46,329 --> 00:10:48,296
BOY: Where were you
aiming at, you idiot?

207
00:10:48,329 --> 00:10:49,763
Go get the ball.

208
00:11:01,196 --> 00:11:03,196
TEACHER: Arisawa,
what's the holdup?

209
00:11:03,229 --> 00:11:03,829
-Nothing, sir.

210
00:11:14,563 --> 00:11:16,029
ULQUIORRA (VOICEOVER):
Don't forget.

211
00:11:16,063 --> 00:11:19,863
You can say goodbye to one
person and one person only.

212
00:11:55,840 --> 00:11:57,261
[static noise]

213
00:11:57,261 --> 00:11:57,961
[beep]

214
00:11:57,994 --> 00:11:59,028
-That's strange.

215
00:11:59,061 --> 00:12:02,561
I can't reach Orihime
in the Soul Society.

216
00:12:02,594 --> 00:12:05,728
Maybe there's some
spiritual wave interference.

217
00:12:05,761 --> 00:12:06,728
[sighs]

218
00:12:19,594 --> 00:12:21,028
HACHIGEN (VOICEOVER): I'm sorry.

219
00:12:21,061 --> 00:12:23,994
This is the best I can do.

220
00:12:24,028 --> 00:12:26,128
My ability doesn't
actually involve

221
00:12:26,161 --> 00:12:28,594
healing someone's
illness or injuries.

222
00:12:28,628 --> 00:12:31,594
It's more a type
of time reversal.

223
00:12:31,628 --> 00:12:34,461
In order to use my
techniques most effectively,

224
00:12:34,494 --> 00:12:37,894
I must have precise knowledge
of what conditions to reverse.

225
00:12:37,928 --> 00:12:41,394
This is critical to
success or failure.

226
00:12:41,428 --> 00:12:43,494
Right now, Ichigo's
spirit energy

227
00:12:43,528 --> 00:12:46,494
has intermingled with the
spirit energy absorbed

228
00:12:46,528 --> 00:12:48,061
from the Arrancars' attacks.

229
00:12:48,094 --> 00:12:51,694
In his current condition,
this is the best I can do.

230
00:12:51,728 --> 00:12:54,594
In order to get him through
this as quickly as possible,

231
00:12:54,628 --> 00:12:56,428
he needs to be isolated.

232
00:12:56,461 --> 00:12:58,361
It's important that
he be separated

233
00:12:58,394 --> 00:13:02,094
from beings like ourselves since
we all have spirit energy that

234
00:13:02,128 --> 00:13:04,128
is similar to the
kind found in Hollows.

235
00:13:04,161 --> 00:13:09,194
Being around us will only slow
down or reverse his recovery.

236
00:13:09,228 --> 00:13:12,228
So my advice to you is
to take him home and let

237
00:13:12,261 --> 00:13:14,494
him rest for as
long as necessary.

238
00:13:14,528 --> 00:13:19,394
That would be the best
treatment for him right now.

239
00:13:19,428 --> 00:13:21,761
RUKIA (VOICEOVER):
Yes, I understand.

240
00:13:26,294 --> 00:13:28,494
Ichigo.

241
00:13:28,528 --> 00:13:31,128
I wonder who those people were.

242
00:13:31,161 --> 00:13:34,628
And even more importantly,
what kind of power

243
00:13:34,661 --> 00:13:38,361
were you trying to
obtain from them?

244
00:13:38,394 --> 00:13:41,061
Why did the Arrancars retreat
in the middle of the fight?

245
00:13:41,094 --> 00:13:43,661
It doesn't make sense.

246
00:13:43,694 --> 00:13:46,361
There are so many things
I don't understand.

247
00:13:50,828 --> 00:13:52,928
All right, Ichigo
will be safe here.

248
00:13:52,961 --> 00:13:54,194
I better go check on Orihime.

249
00:13:54,228 --> 00:13:55,094
KARIN: We shouldn't
be bothering him--

250
00:13:55,128 --> 00:13:55,694
-Huh?

251
00:13:55,728 --> 00:13:56,561
KARIN: --Yuzu.

252
00:13:56,594 --> 00:13:58,194
We were supposed
to let him rest.

253
00:13:58,228 --> 00:14:00,628
YUZU: But, Karin,
what if he wakes up?

254
00:14:00,661 --> 00:14:01,594
We should be there.

255
00:14:01,628 --> 00:14:04,128
He should see somebody
he knows, right?

256
00:14:04,161 --> 00:14:05,061
KARIN: Maybe.

257
00:14:05,094 --> 00:14:06,028
[both gasp]

258
00:14:09,461 --> 00:14:14,894
-Um, Rukia, would it be OK
if we eat dinner in here?

259
00:14:14,928 --> 00:14:17,028
-Hm, of course.

260
00:14:17,061 --> 00:14:18,828
I don't see why not.

261
00:14:18,861 --> 00:14:21,628
