00:15:16,561 --> 00:15:17,661
D-ah!

290
00:15:17,694 --> 00:15:20,028
Mr. Kurosaki, I didn't
know you were still up.

291
00:15:20,061 --> 00:15:21,594
-Good evening there, Rukia.

292
00:15:21,628 --> 00:15:23,594
How's my idiot son doing?

293
00:15:23,628 --> 00:15:24,628
-He's fine.

294
00:15:24,661 --> 00:15:26,328
Of course, he's still sleeping.

295
00:15:26,361 --> 00:15:28,328
-Ahh, don't worry about him.

296
00:15:28,361 --> 00:15:31,694
It's his own stupid fault he
got beat up by some bullies.

297
00:15:31,728 --> 00:15:32,828
I mean, how pathetic.

298
00:15:32,861 --> 00:15:35,961
They're not even
from his school.

299
00:15:35,994 --> 00:15:37,694
-I'm sorry, Mr. Kurosaki.

300
00:15:37,728 --> 00:15:40,061
I mean, this only
happened because I

301
00:15:40,094 --> 00:15:42,028
got him involved with
those delinquents.

302
00:15:42,061 --> 00:15:44,061
-What are you
talking about, Rukia?

303
00:15:44,094 --> 00:15:45,728
The kid's old enough
to know better.

304
00:15:45,761 --> 00:15:47,494
I'm just glad that you're safe.

305
00:15:47,528 --> 00:15:48,628
[fizzing]

306
00:15:48,661 --> 00:15:49,128
I got it!

307
00:15:49,161 --> 00:15:49,794
